text.tspan: Unemployed jobseekers relying on contacts for job search
Proportion of unemployed workers who rely on personal contacts (friends, relatives and trade unions) to search
for a job. Job search methods are not mutually exclusive (i.e. jobseekers may report using multiple methods in
their job search). Estimates come from the European Union Labour Force Survey (EU-LFS), years 2006-2008.
